falls short. This lively living history is grounded in relatable, in-depth interviews that give voice to the millions of Americans building family structures outside the protections of marriage—whether by choice, necessity, or exclusion. Culhane proposes an updated legal status that offers flexible and portable benefits for a diverse range of commitments and needs. As More Than Marriage shows, this ";choose your own adventure"; structure more accurately reflects, and more equitably protects, the many kinds of families we choose to build.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCouplesxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 0aGay couplesxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 0aGay-parent familiesxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aUnmarried couplesxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 7aLAW / Family Law / Marriage.2bisacsh  aColorado Designated Beneficiary Agreement Act.  aDefense of Marriage Act.  aLGBTQ.  aObergefell Hodges.  acivil union.  adomestic partnership.  afamily law.  agay and lesbian couples.  alegal history of marriage protection.  amarriage rights and equality.  amodern families.  aqueer history.  asupreme court.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishz978311131914808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023z9783111318226oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520391673?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520391673423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter